	ethanol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	storage and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	leased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	railcar assets contributed by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Green Plains
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in connection with the IPO on July 1, 2015. References to our &#x201C;sponsor&#x201D; in transactions subsequent to the IPO refer to Green Plains.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Formation and Initial Public Offering
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	and Subsequent Drop Downs
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are a master limited partnership formed by our parent on March 2, 2015. On July 1, 2015, we completed our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	IPO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,500,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	common units representing limited partner interests. Our common units are traded under the symbol &#x201C;GPP&#x201D; on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Nasdaq. After completing the IPO, in addition to the interests of BlendStar,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	we received the assets and liabilities of the ethanol storage and leased railcar assets, previously owned and operated by our parent, in a transfer between entities under common control.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	On
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	January 1, 2016, we acquired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	eth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	anol storage and leased railcar assets of the Hereford, Texas and Hopewell, Virginia ethanol production facilities from our sponsor in a transfer between entities under common control. The assets were recognized at historical cost and reflected retroactively along with related expenses for periods prior to the effective date of the acquisition, subsequent to the initial dates the assets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	were acquired by our sponsor, on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	October 23, 2015, and November 12, 2015, for Hopewell and Hereford, respectively. There were no revenues related to these assets for periods before January 1, 2016, when amendments to our commercial agreements related to the drop down became effective.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	On September 23, 2016, we acquired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ethanol storage assets located in Madison, Illinois; Mount Vernon, Indiana and York, Nebraska related to three ethanol plants, which occurred concurrently with the acquisition of these facilities by Green Plains from subsidiaries of Abengoa S.A. The transaction was accounted for as a transfer between entities under common control and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the assets were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	recognized at the preliminary value recorded in Green Plains&#x2019; purchase accounting. No retroactive adjustments were required.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Green Plains Partners provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fuel storage and transportation services by owning, operating, developing and acquiring ethanol and fuel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	storage facilitie
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s, terminals, transportation assets and other related assets and businesses.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We were formed by Green Plains, a vertically integrated ethanol producer, to support its marketing and distribution activities as its primary downstream logistics provider.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We generate a substantial portion of our revenues under fee-based commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade for receiving, storing, transferring and transporting ethanol and other fuels, which are supported by minimum volume or take-or-pay capacity commitments. We do not take ownership or receive any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	payments based on the value of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	thanol or other fuels we handle. A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s a result, we do not have direct exposure to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fluctuating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	commodity prices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our Assets and Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Ethanol Storage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our ethanol storage assets are the principal method of storing ethanol produced at our parent&#x2019;s ethanol production plants.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Most
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of our parent&#x2019;s ethanol production plants are located
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	near
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	major rail lines.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Ethanol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	can be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	distributed from our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	storage facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to bulk terminals via truck
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	railcar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or barge
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	lease 39 ethanol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	storage facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	nd approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	56
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#FF0000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	acres of land. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	storage tanks
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	located at or near
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our parent&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	17
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ethanol production plants in Indiana,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Illinois,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Iowa, Michigan, Min
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	nesota, Nebraska,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Tennessee

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

These plants allow us to access markets through multiple class one railroads, truck or barge.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Minimum Volume Commitments.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our storage and throughput agreement and certa
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in terminal services agreements with Green Plains Trade
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are supported by minimum volume commitments. Our rail transportation services agreement is supported by minimum take-or-pay capacity commitments. Green Plains Trade is required to pay us fees for these minimum commitments regardless of actual throughput or volume, capacity used or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	amount of product tendered for transport,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which is intended to provide some assurance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	receive a certain amount of revenue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	during the terms of these agreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	he nature of these arrang
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ements is intended to provide stable and predictable cash flows over time.
</FONT>

</FONT>

	the rail transportation services agreement
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

	.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

	Our s

	torage and throughput agreement

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and certain terminal services ag

	reements

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are supported
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	by minimum volume commitments, and o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ur rail transportation services agreement is supported by minimum take-or-pay capacity commitments. Green Plains Trade is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	obligated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to pay us fees for these minimum commitments regardless of actual throughput or volume, capacity used or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	amount of pr
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	oduct tendered for transport
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and the related agreements with Green Plains Trade include minimum volume or take-or-pay capacity commitments. Furthermore, as general partner and owner of a 62.5% limited partner interest in us and all of our incentive distribution rights, our parent directly benefits from our growth, which provides incentive to pursue projects that directly or indirectly enhance the value of our business and assets. This can be accomplished th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ough organic expansion, accretive acquisitions
</FONT>

	or the
</FONT>

</FONT>

	the
</FONT>

	omnibus agreement, we are granted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	right

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Financial Strength and Flexibility.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;Our borrowing capacity and ability to access debt and equity capital markets provide financial flexibility necessary to achieve our organic and acquisition growth strategies.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Proven Management Team.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	commercial,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	operational and financial expertise of our senior management team, which averages

	more than

	s

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Business Strategy
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We believe ethanol could become an increasingly larger portion of the global fuel supply driven by volatile oil prices, heightened environmental concerns, energy independence and national security concerns. We intend to further develop and strengthen our business by pursuing the following growth strategies:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Generate Stable, Fee-Based Cash Flows
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A substantial portion of our revenues and cash flows are derived from our commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade. Under these agreements, we do not have direct exposure to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fluctuating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	commodity prices. We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	intend to continue to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	establish fee-based contracts with our parent and third parties that generate stable and predictable cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Grow Organically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We will collaborate with our parent and other potential third-party customers to identify opportunities to construct assets that provide us long-term returns on our investment. Plant expansion that increases our parent&#x2019;s production capacity also increases annual throughput at our facilities. Capital expenditures associated with expansion are minimal since our ethanol storage facilities have available capacity to accommodate volume growth.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Acquire Strategic Assets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We intend to pursue strategic acquisitions independently and jointly with our parent to grow our business. Our parent has a proven history of identifying, acquiring and integrating assets that are accretive to its business. Under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	omnibus agreement, we have a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	right of first offer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, for a period of five years from the date of the IPO,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	on any fuel storage, terminal or transportation asset our parent owns, constructs or acquires and decides to sell. In addition, we intend to continually monitor the marketplace to identify and pursue assets that complement or diversify our existing operations, including fuel storage and terminal assets in close proximity to our existing asset base.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	January 1, 2016, we acquired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ethanol storage and leased railcar assets of the Hereford, Texas and Hopewell, Virginia ethanol production facilities from our parent for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$62.3 million. We used our revolving credit facility and cash on hand to fund the purchase. The acquired assets include three ethanol storage tanks that support the plants&#x2019; combined production capacity of approximately 160 mmgy and 224 leased railcars with volumetric capacity of approximately 6.7 mmg. We amended the storage and throughput agreement with Green Plains Trade, increasing the
</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	minimum volume commitment from 212.5 mmg to 246.5 mmg per calendar quarter. We also adjusted the rail transportation services agreement, increasing the minimum railcar volumetric capacity commitment 6.7 mmg to 79.6 mmg.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On June 14, 2016, our parent and Jefferson Gulf Coast Energy Partners, a subsidiary of Fortress Transportation and Infrastructure Investors LLC, announced the formation of a 50/50 joint venture to construct and operate an intermodal export and import fuels terminal at Jefferson&#x2019;s existing Beaumont, Texas terminal.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The joint venture is expected to invest approximately $55 million in its Phase I development, which will initially focus on storage and throughput capabilities for m
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ultiple grades of ethanol. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	terminal will have direct access to multiple transportation options, including Aframax vessels, inland and coastwise barges, trucks, and unit trains with direct mainline service from the Union Pacific, BNSF and K
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	CS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	railroads. Green Plains will offer its interest in the joint venture to the partnership once commercial development is complete, which is expected during the second half of 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On August 25, 2016, the partnership filed a shelf registration statement on Form S-3 with the SEC, registering an indeterminate number of debt and equity securities with a total offering price not to exceed $500,000,250 that was declared effective September 2, 2016. The partnership also registered 13,513,500 common units, consisting of 4,389,642 common units and 9,123,858 common units that may be issued upon conversion of subordinated units, in each case, currently held by Green Plains.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On September 23, 2016, we acquired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ethanol storage assets located in Madison, Illinois; Mount Vernon, Indiana and York, Nebraska for $90 million related to three ethanol plants, which occurred concurrently with the acquisition of these facilities by Green Plains from subsidiaries of Abengoa S.A. The acquired assets include ethanol storage tanks that support the plants&#x2019; combined annual production capacity of approximately 236 million gallons. We used our amended revolving credit facility to fund the purchase.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We amended the storage and throughput agreement with Green Plains Trade, increasing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the minimum volume commitment from 246.5 mmg to 296.6 mmg per calendar quarter.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in the Little Rock, Arkansas area
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	capable of unloading 110-car unit trains in less than 24 hours.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tics LLC, a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	50/50 joint venture
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	he project
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is expected to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	be completed in the second half of 2017

	at a

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	total
</FONT>

	cost of approximately $6.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, subject to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	issuance of various
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	permits and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	execution of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	other necessary agreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our Competition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our contractual relationship with Green Plains Trade and the integrated nature of our storage tanks with our parent&#x2019;s production facilities minimizes potential competition for storage and distribution services provided under our commercial agreements from other third-party operators.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We compete with independent fuel terminal operators and major fuel producers for terminal services based on terminal location, services provided, safety and cost. While there are numerous fuel producers and distributors that own terminal operations similar to ours, they are not typically focused on providing services to third parties. Independent operators
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	often
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	located near key distribution points with cost advantages and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	provide more efficient services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	distribution capabilities into strategic markets with a variety of transportation options. Companies often rely on independent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	operators
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	when their own
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	storage facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cannot handle their volumes or manage their throughput adequately due to lack of expertise, market congestion, size constraints, optionality or the nature of the material
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	being stored.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We believe we are well-positioned to compete effectively in a growing market due to our expertise managing third-party terminal services and logistics. We are a low-cost operator, focused on safety and efficiency, capable of managing the needs of multiple constituencies across geographical markets. While the competitiveness of our services can be impacted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	competition from new entrants, transportation constraints, industry production levels and related storage needs, we believe there are significant barriers to entry that partially mitigate these risks, including significant capital costs, execution risk, complex permitting requirements, development cycle, financial and working capital constraints,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	expertise and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	experience
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and ability to effectively capture strategic assets or locations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Seasonality
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our business is directly affected by the supply and demand for ethanol and other fuels in the markets served by our assets. However,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	effects of seasonality on our revenues
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	substantially mitigated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our fee-based commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which include minimum
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	volume or take-or-pay capacity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	commitments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Major
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Customer
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenues from Green Plains Tra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	de
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	totaled approximately $95.5 million, or 92.0%, and $42.5 million, or 83.5%, of our consolidated revenues
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	during 2016 and 2015, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are highly dependent on Green Plains Trade
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	expect to derive most of our revenues from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	them
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the foreseeable future. Accordingly, we are indirectly subject to the business risks of Green Plains Trade
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any development that materially and adversely affects
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	operations, financial condition or market reputation could have a material adverse impact on us.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	For additional information
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, please read
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Risk Factors&#x2014;Risks Related to Our Business
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Regulatory
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Matters
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Government Ethanol Programs and Policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are sensitive to government programs and policies that affect the demand for ethanol and other fuels, which in turn may impact the volume of ethanol and other fuels we handle. In the United States, the federal government mandates the use of renewable fuels under RFS II. The EPA assigns individual refiners, blenders and importers the volume of renewable fuels they are obligated to use based on their percentage of total fuel sales.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The EPA has the authority to waive the mandates in whole or in part if there is inadequate domestic renewable fuel supply, or the requirement severely harms the economy or the environment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	RFS II has been a driving factor in the growth of ethanol usage in the United States. When RFS II was established in October 2010, the required volume of renewable fuel to be blended with gasoline was to increase each year until it reached 15.0 billion gallons in 2015, which left the EPA to address existing limitations in both supply (ethanol production) and demand (usage of ethanol blends in older vehicles). On November 23, 2016, the EPA announced the final 2017 renewable volume obligations for conventional ethanol, which met the 15.0-billion-gallon
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	congressional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	target for the first time, up from 14.50 billion gallons in 2016 and 14.05 billion gallons in 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In January 2017, the Trump administration imposed a government-wide freeze on new and pending regulations, which included the 2017 renewable volume obligations that was originally intended to go into effect on February 10, 2017. Regulatory freezes are a common practice during a change in administration and we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	currently
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	believe the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	new
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	presidential
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	administration will continue to be supportive of ethanol in accordance with the current laws.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On January 18, 2017,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Valero Energy Corporation filed an action against the EPA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	seeking to compel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the EPA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to perform
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	certain
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	non-discretionary duti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	es required
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	by the RFS program under the Clean Air Act.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Within the filed action, Valero claims t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	he EPA has failed to appropriately perform these duties
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	namely periodic reviews of the feasibility of achieving compliance with the requirements and the impact of the requirements on each individual and entity regulated under the program, i.e, point of obligation,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	since 2010.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Valero
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	has requested
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	n injunction, which if granted would require
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	EPA to promptly conduct rulemaking to ensure the requirements of the program are met
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Environmental Regulation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our operations are subject to environmental regulations, including those that govern the handling and release of ethanol, crude oil and other liquid hydrocarbon materials. Compliance with existing and anticipated environmental laws and regulations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	increase our overall cost of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	doing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	business, including capital costs to construct, maintain, operate, and up
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	grade equipment and facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Under the omnibus agreement, our parent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is required to indemnify
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	us from all known and certain unknown environmental liabilities associated with owning and operating our assets that occurred on or before the closing of the IPO. In turn, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	agree
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to indemnify our parent from future environmental liabilities associated with the activities of the partnership.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Construction or maintenance of our terminal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	storage facilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	may impact wetlands, which are regulated by the EPA and the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers under the Clean Water Act.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other Regulations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	O
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	n May 1, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the DOT finalized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	he Enhanced Tank Car Standards and Operational Controls for High-Hazard Flammable Trains
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	DOT specification 117
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, which established
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a schedule to retrofit or replace older tank cars that carry crude oil and ethanol
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	braking standards intended to reduce the severity of accidents and new operational protocols.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The rule may increase our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	lease costs for railcars over the long term. Additionally, existing railcars
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	may be out of service for an
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	extended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	period of time while upgrades are made, tightening supply in an industry that is highly dependent on railcars to transport product. We intend to strategically manage our leased railcar fleet to comply with the new regulations. Currently, all of our railcar leases expire prior to the retrofit deadline of May 1, 2023.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We do not have any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	direct
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	employees.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are managed and operated by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	executive officers of our general partner, who are also officers of our parent, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	general partner&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	board of directors.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	O
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ur general partner and its affiliates
</FONT>

	ly 35 full-time equivalent employees

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	It
</FONT>
<A NAME="GPP-20161231X10K_HTM_ITEM1A_RISKFACTORS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	em 1A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Risk Factors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Investing in our common units involves a high degree of risk. Y
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ou should carefully consider the risks described below together with the other information set forth in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	report
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	before making an investment decision. Any of the following risks and uncertainties could have a material adverse effect on our financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and ability to make distributions to our unitholders. If that occurs, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	not be able to pay distributions on our common units, the trading price of our common units could decline materially, and you could lose all or part of your investment. Although many of our business risks are comparable to those faced by a corporation engaged in a similar business, limited partner interests are inherently different from the capital stock of a corporation and involve additional risks described below. We may experience additional risks and uncertainties not currently known to us or as a result of developments occurring in the future. Conditions that we currently deem to be immaterial may also materially and adversely affect our financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and ability to make distributions to our unitholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Risks Related to Our Business and Industry
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We may not have sufficient cash from operations following the establishment of cash reserves and payment of fees and expenses, including cost reimbursements to our general partner and its affiliates, to pay the minimum quarterly distribution to our unitholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In order to pay the minimum quarterly distribut
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ion of $0.40 per unit per quarter, or $1.60 per unit on an annualized basis, we require available cash of approximately $13.0 million per quarter, or approximately $51.9 million per year, based on the 2% general partner interest and the number of comm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	on units and subordinated units outstanding. We may not have sufficient available cash each quarter to pay the minimum quarterly distribution. The amount of cash we can distribute on our units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	depends
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	on the amount of cash we generate from our operations, which fluctuate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	from quarter to quarter based on:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	The services we provide under commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade account for a substantial portion of our revenues
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	, which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	subject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	us
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the business risks of Green Plains Trade and, as a result of its direct ownership by our parent, to the business risks of our parent.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	entered
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	into a storage and throughput agreement and two transportation services agreements with Green Plains Trade in connection with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the IPO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. Green Plains Trade&#x2019;s obligations under such commercial agreements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	guaranteed by our parent. Additionally, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	assumed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	all of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	BlendStar&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	terminal services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	agreements with Green Plains Trade. The services we provide under commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade account for a substantial portion of our revenues for the foreseeable future
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	therefore
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	we are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	subject to risk of nonpayment or nonperformance by Green Plains Trade and our parent under the commercial agreements. Any event, whether related to our operations or otherwise, that materially and adversely affects Green Plains Trade&#x2019;s or our parent&#x2019;s financial condition, results of operations or cash flows may adversely affect our ability to sustain or increase cash distributions to our unitholders. Accordingly, we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	indirectly subject to the following operational and business risks of our parent and its subsidiaries (including Green Plains Trade), among others:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Ethanol production and marketing is a highly competitive business subject to changing market demands and regulatory environments. Any change in our parent&#x2019;s business or financial strategy to meet such demands or requirements may negatively impact our parent&#x2019;s financial condition, results of operations or cash flows and, in turn, may adversely affect our financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and ability to make distributions to our unitholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Ethanol production, storage and transportation, and marketing is highly competitive. In the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	United States
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, our parent&#x2019;s operations compete with other corn processors and refiners. Some of our parent&#x2019;s competitors are larger than our parent, and there are also many smaller competitors. Farm cooperatives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	comprised of groups of individual farmers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	have been able to compete successfully in the ethanol production industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. As of December 31, 2016, the top five domestic producers accounted for approximately 45% of all production, with production capaciti
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	es ranging from approximately 800 mmgy to 1,80
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	0 mmgy. If our parent&#x2019;s competitors consolidate or other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	wise gr
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ow or our parent is unable to similarly increase its size and scope, our parent&#x2019;s business and prospects may be significantly and adversely affected. Additionally, there is a risk of forei
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	gn competition in the ethanol industry. Foreign producers, including those in Brazil, the second largest ethanol producer in the world, may be able to produce ethanol at lower input costs, including costs of feedstock, facilities and personnel, than our parent.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Additionally, our parent considers opportunities presented by third parties related to its assets, including its ethanol production plants. These opportunities may include offers to purchase assets and joint venture propositions. Our parent may also change the focus of its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	operations by developing new facilities, suspending or reducing certain operations, modifying or closing facilities or terminating operations. Changes may be considered to meet market demands, to satisfy regulatory requirements or environmental and safety objectives, to improve operational efficiency or for other reasons. Our parent actively manages its assets and operations, and, therefore, changes of some nature, possibly material to its business relationship with us, are likely to occur at some point in the future. No such changes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will be
</FONT>

	subject to our consent.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A change in our parent&#x2019;s business or financial strategy, contractual obligations or risk profile may negatively impact its financial condition, results of operations, cash flows or creditworthiness. In turn, our cash flows from our commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade and, therefore, our ability to sustain or increase cash distributions to our unitholders may be materially and adversely
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	affected. Moreover, our creditworthiness
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may be adversely affected by a decline in our parent&#x2019;s creditworthiness, increasing our borrowing costs or hindering our ability to access the capital markets. Please
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	also refer to the following risk factor in this report: &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our parent&#x2019;s existing debt arrangements requiring it to abide by certain restrictive loan covenants may adversely affect our ability to grow our business, our ability to pay cash distributions to our unitholders and our credit profile. Our ability to obtain credit in the future may also be affected
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	by our parent&#x2019;s credit ratings, our own credit profile and the environment for access to capital for master limited partnerships.&#x201D; A third-party purchaser may identify alternative service providers and opt for minimum volume commitments or minim
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	um take-or-pay capacity commitments or decide to allow the commercial agreements to expire at the end of the original term. Such third party may also operate the ethanol production plants in a suboptimal manner, increasing the frequency of turnarounds and reducing capacity utilization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Furthermore, conflicts of interest may arise between our general partner and its affiliates, including our parent and Green Plains Trade, on the one hand, and us and our unitholders, on the other hand. Green Plains Trade may suspend, reduce or terminate its obligations under the commercial agreements with us in certain circumstances, which could have a material adverse effect on our financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and ability to make di
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	stributions to our unitholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have no control over our parent or Green Plains Trade, which are currently our primary source of revenue and primary customers, and our parent and Green Plains Trade may elect to pursue a business strategy that does not favor us and our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	profitability is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	substantial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	ly dependent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	on our parent&#x2019;s ethanol production plants.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We believe that a substantial portion of our revenues for the foreseeable future will be derived from operations supporting our parent&#x2019;s ethanol production plants. Any event that renders these ethanol production plants temporarily or permanently unavailable or that temporarily or permanently reduces production rates at any of these ethanol production plants could adversely affect our financial condition, results of operations, cash flows and ability to make distributions to our unitholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Green Plains Trade may suspend, reduce or terminate its obligations under the commercial agreements with us in certain circumstances.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	All of our commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade include provisions that permit Green Plains Trade to suspend, reduce or terminate its obligations under the agreements if certain events occur. Under all of our commercial agreements, these events include a material breach of such agreements by us, the occurrence of certain force majeure events that would prevent Green Plains Trade or us from performing our respective obligations under the applicable commercial agreement and the minimum commitment, if any, not being available to Green Plains Trade for any reason not resulting from or relating to an action or inaction by Green Plains Trade.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	If
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, at the end of the remaining primary term, our parent and Green Plains Trade elect not to extend these agreements and, as a result, fail to use our assets and we are unable to generate additional revenues from third parties, our ability to pay cash distributions to our unitholders will be reduced. Furthermore, any renewal of the commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade may not be on favorable commercial terms. For example, depending on prevailing market conditions at the time of contract renewal, Green Plains Trade may desire to enter into contracts under different fee arrangements. To the extent we are unable to renew the commercial agreements with Green Plains Trade on terms that are favorable to us, our revenue and cash flows could decline and our ability to pay cash distributions to our unitholders could be materially and adversely affected.

	Green Plains Trade&#x2019;s minimum take-or-pay capacity commitment will be reduced proportionately

	as our railcar leases expire if

	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	We lease our
</FONT>

	fleet of railcars fr

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	As our railcar lease agreements expire, the respective volumetric capacity of those expired leases will no longer be subject to the rail transportation services agreement, and Green Plains Trade&#x2019;s minimum take-or-pay capacity commitment will be reduced proportionately. Of our current leased railcar fleet,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	8.8%, 34.1%, 10.5% and 15.7%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;BACKGROUND-COLOR:FUCHSIA;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Railcars used to transport ethanol and other fuels may need to be retrofitted or replaced to meet new rail safety standards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The U.S. ethano
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	l industry has long relied on railroads to deliver its product to market. We currently lease approximately 3,100 railcars. On M
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ay 1, 2015, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	DOT
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, through
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	PHMSA and FRA, an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	d in coordination with Transport Canada, announced the final rule, &#x201C;Enhanced Tank Car Standards and Operational Controls for High-Hazard Flammable Trains&#x201D;. The rule calls for an enhanced tank car standard known as the DOT specification 117, or DOT-117 tank car, and establishes a schedule for retrofitting or replacing older tank cars carrying crude oil and ethanol. The rule also establishes new braking standards that are intended to reduce the severity of accidents and the so-called &#x201C;pile-up effect&#x201D;. Under prescribed circumstances, new operational protocols apply including reduced speed, routing requirements and local government notifications. In addition, persons that offer hazardous material for transportation must develop more accurate classification protocols. These regulati
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ons will result in upgrades or replacements of our railcars,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	have an adverse effect on our operations as lease costs for railcars
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	increase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	over the long term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our railcars are also subject to federally-mandated tank car requalification, which requires inspection, repairs and upgrades to our current railcar fleet every ten years. Due to these regulatory standards, as well as any potential modifications that may be issued in the future, e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	xisting rai
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	lcars could be out of service for a period of time while such upgrades are made, tightening supply in an industry that is highly dependent on such railcars to transport its product.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	17
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
