	Mr. Riley is qualified to serve on our general partner&#x2019;s board of directors because of hi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s financial and master limited partnership experience within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a variety of industries
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	John D. Chandler.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	John Chandler
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	was appointed a member of the board of directors of our general partner in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	June
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and serves
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	as a member of both the audit and conflicts committee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Mr. Chandler currently serves on the board of directors and is chair of the audit committee of USA Compression GP, LLC. He is also a member of the board of directors and audit committee of Cone Midstream GP, LLC. From 2002 to 2014, he served as chief financial officer, treasurer and chief accounting officer of Magellan Midstream Holdings GP. Before joining Magellan, Mr. Chandler was director, planning and strategic development for a subsidiary of The Williams Companies, Inc. and held various accounting and finance positions at MAPCO Inc. Mr. Chandler earned a Bachelor of Science in Business Adminis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tration with a double major in Accounting and F
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	inance from the University of Tulsa.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Mr. Chandler is qualified to serve on our general partner&#x2019;s board of directors because of hi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s financial and master limited partnership experience within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a variety of industries
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Board of Directors Leadership Structure
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The board of directors of our general partner has no policy with respect to the separation of the offices of chairman of the board of directors and chief executive officer. Instead, that relationship is defined and governed by the limited liability company agreement of our general partner, which permits the same person to hold both offices. Directors of the board of directors of our general partner are designated or elected by our parent. Accordingly, unlike holders of common stock in a corporation, our unitholders
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	only limited voting rights on matters affecting our business or governance, subject in all cases to any specific unitholder rights contained in our partnership agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Board of Directors Role in Risk Oversight
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our corporate governance guidelines
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	state
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the board of directors of our general partner is responsible for reviewing the process
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	assessing major risks facing us and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	options for their mitigation. This responsibility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	largely satisfied by our audit committee, which is responsible for reviewing and discussing with management and our registered public accounting firm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	major risk exposures and the policies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	implemented by management to monitor such exposures. This includes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our financial risk exposures and risk management policies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compliance with Section 16(a) of the Exchange Act
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Section 16(a) of the Exchange Act requires our general partner's officers and directors and persons who beneficially own more than 10% of our common units to file reports of securities ownership and changes in such ownership with the SEC. Officers, directors and greater than 10% beneficial owners are also required by rules promulgated by the SEC to furnish us with copies of all Section 16(a) forms they file. Based solely upon a review of the Forms 3 and 4, including any amendm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ents, filed with the SEC in 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(no Forms 5, or any amendments,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	were filed with respect to 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	), all required report filings by our (or our general partner's) directors and executive officers and greater than 10% affiliated beneficial owners were timely made.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Code of Ethics
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR:LIME;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The board of directors of our general partner has adopted a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	code of e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	thics which sets forth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the partnership&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	policy with respect to business ethics
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and conflicts of interest. The c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ode of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	thics is intended to ensure that the employees, officers and directors of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the partnership
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	conduct business with the highest standards of integrity and in compliance with all applicable laws and regulations. It applies to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	employees, officers and directors of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the partnership
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, including its principal executive officer, principal financial officer and controller, or pers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ons performing similar functions. The code of e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	thics also in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	corporates expectations of the senior financial o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fficers that enable us to provide accurate and timely disclosure in our filings with the SEC and ot
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	her public communications. The code of e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	thics is publicly available on our website under the "Corporate Governance" subsection of the Investors section at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	www.greenplainspartners.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and is also available free of charge on request to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Secretary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	at the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Omaha
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	office address given under the "Contact" section on our website.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Overview &#x2013; Compensation Decisions and Allocation of Compensation Expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Neither the partnership nor the general partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	employ any of the persons responsible for managing our business.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our general partner does not have a compensation committee. O
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ur general partner, under the direction of its board of directors, is responsible for managing our operations and for obtaining the services of the employees that operate our business.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	nt. We are responsible for paying the long-term incentive compensation expense associated with our LTIP described below. T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	he
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	NEOs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	continue to participate in employee benefit plans and arrangements sponsored by our parent, including plans that may be established in the future. Our general partner has not entered into any employment agreements with any of its executive officers.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	There was no compensation in any form paid to or earned by any executive officer of our general partner in 2016 or 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	All compensation was paid by our parent and allocated to the partnership through our corporate allocation process.
</FONT>

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	compensation allocation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	Amounts for 2016 are expected to be finalized subsequent to the date of this report. Once finalized, such amounts will be disclosed in a filing under Item 5.02 of Form 8-K.&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&#xFEFF;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Outstanding Equity Awards at Year-End
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	There were no outstanding equity awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	NEOs as of December 31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our Long-Term Incentive Plan
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our general partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	adopted our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for officers, directors and employees of our general partner or its affiliates, and any consultants, affiliates of our general partner or other individuals who perform services for us. Our general partner may issue long-term equity based awards under the plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our executive officers and other service providers. These awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	intended to compensate the recipients based on the performance of our common units and the recipient&#x2019;s continued service during the vesting period, as well as to align recipients&#x2019; long-term interests with those of our unitholders. The plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	administered by the board of directors of our general partner or any committee thereof that may be established for such purpose or to which the board of directors or such committee may delegate such authority, subject to applicable law. All determinations with respect to awards to be made under our LTIP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	made by the plan administrator and we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	responsible for the cost of awards granted under our LTIP. The following description summarizes the terms of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP, but this summary does not purport to be a complete description of all of the provisions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	General
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for the grant, from time to time at the discretion of the plan administrator or any delegate thereof, subject to applicable law, of unit awards, restricted units, phantom units, unit options, unit appreciation rights, distribution equivalent rights, profits interest units and other unit-based awards. The purpose of awards under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP is to provide additional incentive compensation to employees and any other individuals providing services to us, and to align the economic interests of such employees and individuals with the interests of our unitholders. The plan administrator may grant awards under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP to reward the achievement of individual or partnership performance goals; however, no specific performance goals that might be utilized for this purpose have yet been determined. In addition, the plan administrator may grant awards under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP without regard to performance factors or conditions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP will limit the number of units that may be delivered pursuant to vested awards to 2,500,000 common units, subject to proportionate adjustment in the event of unit splits and similar events. Common units subject to awards that are cancelled, forfeited, withheld to satisfy exercise prices or tax withholding obligations or otherwise terminated without delivery of the common units will be available for delivery pursuant to other awards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Restricted Units and Phantom Units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. A restricted unit is a common unit that is subject to forfeiture. Upon vesting, the forfeiture restrictions lapse and the recipient holds a common unit that is not subject to forfeiture. A phantom unit is a notional unit that entitles the grantee to receive a common unit upon the vesting of the phantom unit or on a deferred basis upon specified future dates or events or, in the discretion of the plan administrator, cash equal to the fair market value of a common unit. The plan administrator of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP may make grants of restricted and phantom units under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP that contain such terms, consistent with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP, as the plan administrator may determine are appropriate, including the period over which restricted or phantom units will vest. The plan administrator may, in its discretion, base vesting on the grantee&#x2019;s completion of a period of service or upon the achievement of specified financial objectives or other criteria or upon a change in control (as defined in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP) or as otherwise described in an award agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Distributions made by us with respect to awards of restricted units may be subject to the same vesting requirements as the restricted units.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Distribution Equivalent Rights.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The plan administrator, in its discretion, may also grant distribution equivalent rights, either as standalone awards or in tandem with other awards. Distribution equivalent rights are rights to receive an amount in cash, restricted units or phantom units equal to all or a portion of the cash distributions made on units during the period an award remains outstanding.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Unit Options and Unit Appreciation Rights.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP also permits the grant of options and appreciation rights covering common units. Unit options represent the right to purchase a number of common units at a specified exercise price. Unit appreciation rights represent the right to receive the appreciation in the value of a number of common units over a specified exercise price, either in cash or in common units. Unit options and unit appreciation rights may be granted to such eligible individuals and with such terms as the plan administrator may determine, consistent with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP; however, a unit option or unit appreciation right must have an exercise price equal to at least the fair market value of a common unit on the date of grant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Unit Awards.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards covering common units may be granted under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP with such terms and conditions, including
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	61
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage63"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#GPP-20161231X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	restrictions on transferability, as the administrator of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP may establish.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Profits Interest Units.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Awards granted to grantees who are partners, or granted to grantees in anticipation of the grantee becoming a partner or granted as otherwise determined by the administrator, may consist of profits interest units. The administrator will determine the applicable vesting dates, conditions to vesting and restrictions on transferability and any other restrictions for profits interest awards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Other Unit-Based Awards.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP may also permit the gra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	nt of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	other unit-based awards, which are awards that, in whole or in part, are valued or based on or related to the value of a common unit. The vesting of other unit-based award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may be based on a participant&#x2019;s continued service, the achievement of performance criteria or other measures. On vesting or on a deferred basis upon specified future dates or events, other unit-based award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may be paid in cash and/or in units (including restricted units), or any combination thereof as the plan administrator may determine.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Source of Common Units.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Common units to be delivered with respect to awards may be newly issued units, common units acquired by us or our general partner in the open market, common units already owned by our general partner or us, common units acquired by our general partner directly from us or any other person or any combination of the foregoing.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Anti-Dilution Adjustments and Change in Control.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If an &#x201C;equity restructuring&#x201D; event occurs that could result in an additional compensation expense under applicable accounting standards if adjustments to awards under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP with respect to such event were discretionary, the plan administrator will equitably adjust the number and type of units covered by each outstanding award and the terms and conditions of such award to equitably reflect the restructuring event and will adjust the number and type of units with respect to which future awards may be granted under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP. With respect to other similar events, including, for example, a combination or exchange of units, a merger or consolidation or an extraordinary distribution of our assets to unitholders, that would not result in an accounting charge if adjustment to awards were discretionary, the plan administrator shall have discretion to adjust awards in the manner it deems appropriate and to make equitable adjustments, if any, with respect to the number of units available under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP and the kind of units or other securities available for grant under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP. Furthermore, upon any such event, including a change in control of us or our general partner, or a change in any law or regulation affecting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP or outstanding awards or any relevant change in accounting principles, the plan administrator will generally have discretion to (i) accelerate the time of exercisability or vesting or payment of an award, (ii) require awards to be surrendered in exchange for a cash payment or substitute other rights or property for the award, (iii) provide for the award to assumed by a successor or one of its affiliates, with appropriate adjustments thereto, (iv) cancel unvested awards without payment or (v) make other adjustments to awards as the administrator deems appropriate to reflect the applicable transaction or event.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Termination of Service.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The consequences of the termination of a grantee&#x2019;s employment, membership on our general partner&#x2019;s board of directors or other service arrangement will generally be determined by the plan administrator in the terms of the relevant award agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Amendment or Termination of Long-Term Incentive Plan.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The plan administrator, at its discretion, may terminate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP at any time with respect to the common units for which a grant has not previously been made. The plan administrator also has the right to alter or amend
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP or any part of it from time to time or to amend any outstanding award made under
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	LTIP, provided that no change in any outstanding award may be made that would materially impair the vested rights of the participant without the consent of the affected participant or result in taxation to the partici
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	pant under Section 409A of the Internal Revenue Code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compensation Consultants
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The board of directors of our general partner does not have a compensation committee, and it did not retain a compensation consultant in 2016 or 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Insider Trading Policy
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our board of directors has adopted an insider trading policy both to satisfy the partnership&#x2019;s obligation to prevent insider trading and to help partnership insiders avoid the severe consequences associated with violations of insider trading laws. As the partnership has worked diligently to establish a reputation for integrity and ethical conduct, this policy is also intended to prevent even the appearance of improper conduct on the part of anyone associated with the partnership.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	No director, officer or employee of the partnership who is aware of material nonpublic information relating to the partnership may, directly or through family members or other persons or entities, (a) buy or sell securities of the partnership
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	62
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage64"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#GPP-20161231X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(other than pursuant to a pre-approved trading plan that complies with SEC Rule 10b5-1), or engage in any other action to take personal advantage of that information, or (b) pass that information on to others outside the partnership, including family and friends. In addition, no director, officer or other employee of the partnership who, in the course of working for the partnership, learns of material nonpublic information about a company with which the partnership does business, including a customer or supplier of the partnership, may trade in that company&#x2019;s securities until the information becomes public or is no longer material.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Certain forms of hedging or monetization transactions allow an employee to lock in much of the value of his or her stock holdings, often in exchange for all or part of the potential for upside appreciation in the stock. These transactions allow the director, officer or employee to continue to own the covered securities, but without the full risks and rewards of ownership. When that occurs, the director, officer or employee may no longer have the same objectives as the partnership&#x2019;s other unitholders. Any person wishing to enter into such an arrangement must first pre-clear the proposed transaction with the partnership&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer or his designee.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Securities held in a margin account may be sold by the broker without the customer&#x2019;s consent if the customer fails to meet a margin call. Similarly, securities pledged or hypothecated as collateral for a loan may be sold in foreclosure if the borrower defaults on the loan. Because a margin sale or foreclosure sale may occur at a time when the pledgor is aware of material nonpublic information or otherwise is not permitted to trade in partnership securities, directors, officers and other employees who are aware of material nonpublic information relating to the partnership are prohibited from holding partnership securities in a margin account or pledging partnership securities as collateral for a loan. An exception to this prohibition may be granted where a person wishes to pledge partnership securities as collateral for a loan, not including margin debt, and clearly demonstrates the financial capacity to repay the loan without resort to the pledged securities. Any person who wishes to pledge partnership securities as collateral for a loan must submit a request for approval to the partnership&#x2019;s Chief Executive Officer or his designee at least two weeks prior to the proposed execution of documents evidencing the proposed pledge.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The partnership has applied and interpreted the insider trading policy that hedging and pledging transactions are not permitted, without approval, and approval is not easily achieved or given out just because it was requested. To date, our parent has never approved hedging, and it has allowed just three directors, with one being a past director, to pledge, only after they had demonstrated the necessary financial capacity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Compensation of Our Directors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	O
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ur general partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	adopted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a director compensation policy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, which states
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	directors who
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are not officers, employees or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	paid consultants or advisors of us or our general partner receive a combination of cash and restricted common unit grants as compensation for attending meetings of the board of directors of our general partner and any committees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	meetings as follows:
</FONT>
</P>

	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Security Ownership of Certain Beneficial Owners and Management and Related Stockholder Matters.

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The following table sets forth the beneficial ownership of our units as of February 14, 2017, held by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	i) beneficial owners of 5% or mor
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	e of the units, (ii) each director and named executive officer of our general partner, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(iii) all director and executive officers of our general partner as a group.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The amounts and percentage of units beneficially owned are reported on the basis of regulations of the SEC governing the determination of beneficial ownership of securities. Under the rules of the SEC, a person is deemed to be a beneficial owner of a security if that person has or shares voting power, which includes the power to vote or to direct the voting of such security, or investment power, which includes the power to dispose of or to direct the disposition of such security. In computing the number of common units beneficially owned by a person and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the percentage ownership of that person, common units subject to options or warrants held by that person that are currently exercisable or exercisable within 60 days
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of February 14, 2017, if a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ny, are deemed outstanding, but are not deemed outstanding for computing the percentage ownership of any other person. Except as indicated by footnote, the persons n
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	amed in the table below have sole voting and investment power with respect to all units shown as beneficially owned by them, subject to community property laws where applicable.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	The following table provides information as of December 31, 2016, with respect to the partnership&#x2019;s common units that may be issued under our LTIP.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Operational Stage
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Distributions of available cash to our general partner and its affiliates.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	generally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	make cash distributions to the unitholders, pro rata, including our parent, as holder of an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	4,3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	89,642 common units and 15,889,642 subordinated units. In addition, if distributions exceed the minimum quarterly distribution and target distribution levels, the incentive distribution rights held by our general partner will entitle our general partner to increasing percentages of the distributions, up to 48% (in addition to distributions paid on its 2% general partner interest) of the distributions above the highest target distribution level.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Assuming we generate sufficient distributable cash flow to support the payment of the full minimum quarterly distribution on all of our outstanding units for four quarters, our general partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	receive an annual distribution of approximately $1.0 million on the 2% general partner interest and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our parent will receive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	$3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	million on their common units and subordinated units.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Payments to our general partner and its affiliates.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Under our partnership agreement, we are required to reimburse our general partner and its affiliates for all costs and expenses that they incur on our behalf for managing and controlling our business and operations. Except to the extent specified in the operational services and secondment agreement and omnibus agreement, our general partner determines the amount of these expenses and such determinations must be made in good faith under the terms of our partnership agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Under our operational services and secondment agreement, our general partner reimburse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our parent for the secondment to our general partner of certain employees who serve management, maintenance and operational functions in support of our operations and reimburse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Green Plains for the provision of those personnel, including with respect to routine and emergency maintenance and repair services, routine operational activities, routine administrative services and such other services as we and Green Plains may mutually agree
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	upon
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	from time to time. The costs and expenses for which we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	required to reimburse our general partner and its affiliates
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	not be subject to any caps or other limits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Under our omnibus agreement, we reimburse our parent for all reasonable direct and indirect costs and expenses incurred by our parent and its affiliates in connection with the provision of certain general and administrative services, such as treasury, accounting and legal services. These services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	consistent in nature and quality to the services of such type previously provided by our parent in connection with our assets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Withdrawal or removal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	of our general partner.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If our general partner withdraws or is removed, its incentive distribution rights will either be sold to the new general partner for cash or converted into common units, for an amount equal to the fair market value of such interests.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Liquidation Stage
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Upon our liquidation, the partners, including our general partner, will be entitled to receive liquidating distributions according to their respective capital account balances.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</TD>

<P STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;">

	the partnership&#x2019;s right of first offer to acquire assets if Green Plains decides to sell them for up to five years from the consummation of the IPO;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Subsequent to the IPO,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Green Plains Trucking
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	conveyed their interest in the partnership to Green Plains.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Operating Services and Secondment Agreement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In connection with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	IPO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, the general partner entered into an operational services and secondment agreement with Green Plains
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. Under the terms of the agreement,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Green Plains seconds employees to the general partner to provide management, maintenance and operational functions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	partnership, including
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	regulatory matters, health, environment, safety and security programs, operational services, emergency response, employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	training
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, finance and administration, human resources
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	business operations and planning.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	he seconded personnel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	under the direct management and supervision of the general partner.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The general partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	reimburses
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the parent for the cost of the seconded employees, including wages and benefits. If a seconded employee does not devote 100% of his or her time providing services to the general partner, the general partner reimburse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the parent for a prorated portion of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	employee&#x2019;s overall wages and benefits based on the percentage of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	time the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	spent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	working for the general partner. The parent bill
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the general partner monthly in arrears for services p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	rovided during the prior month. Payment is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	due within 10 days of the general partner&#x2019;s receipt of the invoice.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Under the operational services and secondment agreement, our parent will indemnify us from any claims, losses or liabilities incurred by us, including third-party claims, arising from their performance of the operational services secondment agreement; provided, however, our parent will not be obligated to indemnify us for any claims, losses or liabilities arising out of our gross negligence, willful misconduct or bad faith with respect to any services provided under the operational services and secondment agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Effective January 1, 2016, and September 23, 2016, the operational services and secondment agreement was amended in connection with the acquisition of additional storage and transportation assets. Our general p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	artner entered into
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	an amendment to the operational s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ervices
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and secondment agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our parent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which states
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our parent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will second certain employees to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our general partner
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to provide management, maintenance and operational funct
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ions with respect to the a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ssets. The provided functions will be substantially similar to the management, maintenance and operational functions previously provided under the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	operational services and secondment a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	greement.

	he rail transportation services agreement is supported by minimum take-or-pay capacity commitments. 	, 2016, the rail transportation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	agreement was amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to extend the initial term of the agreement, effective July 1, 2015, from a six-year term to a ten-year term. All other terms and conditions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	remain&nbsp;the same as&nbsp;the&nbsp;initial agreement, as previously amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.

	&#xFEFF;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Effective January 1, 2017, the terminal services agreement for the Birmingham, Alabama unit train terminal was amended and restated. Green Plains Trade is now obligated to pay $0.036 per gallon on all throughput volumes, subject to a minimum commitment of approximately 2.8 mmg per month of ethanol and other fuels, equivalent to 33.2 mmgy, as well as fees for ancillary services through December 31, 2019. Previously, the rate was $0.0355 per gallon.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Procedures for Review, Approval and Ratification of Related Person Transactions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The board of directors of our general partner adopt
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a related party transactions policy in connection with the closing of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the IPO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the board of directors of our general partner or its authorized committee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	will
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	review on at least a quarterly basis all related person transactions that are required to be disclosed under SEC rules and, when appropriate, initially authorize or ratify all such transactions. In the event that the board of directors of our general partner or its authorized committee considers ratification of a related person transaction and determines not to so ratify, the code of business conduct and ethics will provide that our management will make all reasonable efforts to cancel or annul the transaction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The related party transactions policy provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that, in determining whether or not to recommend the initial approval or ratification of a related person transaction, the board of directors of our general partner or its authorized committee should consider all of the relevant facts and circumstances available, including (if applicable) but not limited to: (1) whether there is an appropriate business justification for the transaction; (2) the benefits that accrue to us as a result of the transaction; (3) the terms available to unrelated third parties entering into similar transactions; (4) the impact of the transaction on a director&#x2019;s independence (in the event the related person is a director, an immediate family member of a director or an entity in which a director or an immediate family member of a director is a partner,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	holder, member or executive officer); (5) the availability of other sources for comparable products or services; (6) whether it is a single transaction or a series of ongoing, related transactions; and (7) whether entering into the transaction would be consistent with the code of business conduct and e
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	thics.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	If a conflict or potential conflict of interest arises between our general partner or its affiliates, on the one hand, and us or our unitholders, on the other hand, the resolution of any such conflict or potential conflict should be addressed by the board of directors of our general partner in accordance with the provisions of our partnership agreement. At the discretion of the board in light of the circumstances, the resolution may be determined by the board in its entirety or by a conflicts committee meeting the definitional requirements for such a committee under our partnership agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The information required by Item 407(a) of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Regulation S-K is included in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Item 10 &#x2013;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Directors, Executive Officers and Corporate Governance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	of this report
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Audit fees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	are fees billed by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	KPMG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for services during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2016 and 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	related to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	professional services rendered for the annual audit of our consolidated financial statements, quarterly reviews of our consolidated financial statements, reviews of other partnership filings with the SEC
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and other fees that are normally provided by the independent auditor in connection with statutory and regulatory filings or engagements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Audit-related fees are fees billed by KPMG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for services during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	related to the filing of the partnership&#x2019;s registration statement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Pre-Approval of Audit and Non-Audit Services
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	adopted policies and procedures for pre-approval of all audit and non-audit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	services to be provided
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	independent auditor. It is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	policy
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	that the audit c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ommittee pre-approve all audit, tax and other non-audit services. A proposal for audit or non-audit services must include a description and purpose of the services, estimated fees and other terms of the services. To the extent a proposal relates to non-audit services, a determination that such services qualify as permitted non-audit services and an explanation as to why the provision of such services would not impair the independence of the independent auditor are also required.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	All services provided by KPMG during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the years ended December 31, 2016 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	5,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	were approved in advance by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our audit committee. The audit c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ommittee has considered whether the provision of the services performed by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	principal accountant is compatible with maintaining the principal accountant&#x2019;s independence.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>

<EFX_AUDITORS_OPINION>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDITORS_OPINION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Board of Directors of
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Green Plains Holdings LLC, the general partner of Green Plains Partners LP
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Unitholders of Green Plains Partners LP:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We have audited the accompanying consolidated balance sheets of Green Plains Par
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tners LP and subsidiaries (the p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	artnership) as of December 31, 2016 and 2015, and the related consolidated statements of operations, partners&#x2019; capital, and cash flows for each of the years in the three-year period ended December 31, 2016. These consolidated financial statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	are the responsibility of the p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	artnership&#x2019;s management. Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these consolidated financial statements based on our audits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We conducted our audits in accordance with generally accepted auditing standards as established by the Auditing Standards Board (United States) and in accordance with the auditing standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the financial statements are free
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of material misstatement. The p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	artnership is not required to have, nor were we engaged to perform, an audit of its internal control over financial reporting. Our audit included consideration of internal control over financial reporting as a basis for designing audit procedures that are appropriate in the circumstances, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	p
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	artnership&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no such opinion. An audit also includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the financial statements, assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall financial statement presentation. We believe that our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In our opinion, the consolidated financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the financial position of Green Plains Partners LP and subsidiaries as of December 31, 2016 and 2015, and the results of their operations and their cash flows for the years then ended in conformity with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	As discussed in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Note 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to the consolidated financial statements, the partnership recognized assets and liabilities transferred on January 1, 2016, and September 23, 2016, at the parent&#x2019;s historical cost basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such assets and liabilities and the associated expenses are reflected retroactively, if applicable.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#FF0000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	/s/ KPMG LLP
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.&nbsp;&nbsp;BASIS OF PRESENTATION AND DESCRIPTION OF BUSINESS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
